<p>‚ÄìUnchanged. I‚Äôm not touching that.</p>
<p>‚ÄìMake sure, please, that Highet knows all this. Sometimes he wanders through here and if things are not what he expects he is most unpleasant.</p>
<p>Outside Highet‚Äôs office Quine, arm raised to knock, from within heard Highet‚Äôs insistent rasp, ‚Äìlike <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul%20Kammerer" title="Wikipedia: Paul Kammerer">Kammerer</a>, you know, it‚Äôs not who makes the mistake it‚Äôs who takes the blame, and at Thorpe‚Äôs voice barely audible, ‚Äìsorry for the poor son of a bitch stuck in his position at his age, barely shows his face, and Highet, ‚Äìnever passed a design review, Quine‚Äôs ears flared with heat, the door before him turning flat and insubstantial as he lowered his hand and proceeded down the hall unseeing, guided by a familiarity more the prisoner‚Äôs than the adept‚Äôs [pg35] around a corner to a water fountain, stopped before a bulletin board and its overlapping notices O Section, programmer needed to model underground plumes K Section, LASS expert needed Z Section, multimedia guru sought B Section, materials engineer, while two young men passed, one saying, ‚ÄìI have no special loyalty to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object-oriented%20programming" title="Wikipedia: Object-oriented programming">OOP</a>, and on to a further junction where a convex mirror above him presented an anamorphic view around the corner. There Nan emerged from a cross corridor with a wiry man, white teeth in a tanned face, blackhaired forearms folded. The two spoke briefly. The man put a hand on Nan‚Äôs neck and bent forward to kiss her mouth. Quine turned back the way he had come, slowing only when he found he had nearly circled the building. He backtracked to Highet‚Äôs door and entered without knocking.</p>
<p>‚ÄìGet Thorpe out of my office.</p>
<p>Highet looked up in surprise. ‚ÄìWhat did he do to you, Philip? You look ready to spit.</p>
<p>‚ÄìIf he‚Äôs so important give him his own space, I don‚Äôt want him hanging around me.</p>
<p>‚ÄìThought you‚Äôd appreciate the company, thought he might be useful to you.</p>
