<p>R√©ti‚Äôs voice, slow and heavy with a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austria-Hungary" title="Wikipedia: Austria-Hungary">Transyvlvanian</a> accent unrelinquished after sixty years in America, was the aristocrat to Eubanks‚Äôs plebe. A sales talk all the same, and so what? From Plato to Planck, science was persuasion. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dialogue%20Concerning%20the%20Two%20Chief%20World%20Systems" title="Wikipedia: Dialogue Concerning the Two Chief World Systems">Galileo‚Äôs dialog</a> of Simplicio, Sagredo, and Salviati was written to persuade, not to prove.</p>
