<p>‚ÄìReally? Of course the timing, the appearance of improp</p>
<p>A momentary hish fell on the room, and then a short sharp shock rattled crockery, rippled water in glasses, and set overhead lights swaying. In its wake was a second of silence, and then, outside, car alarms ignited in periodic blasts of horn, sirens ramping up and sweeping down, a buzzing and warbling complexity on the edge of chaos, as conversation tentatively resumed and phones were unfolded and some [pg179] patrons rose and went out into the lot as Jeremy Rector closely examined a duck‚Äôs foot, saying, ‚ÄìI‚Äôll give your offer some thought.</p>
<p>‚ÄìTry the parchment wrapped chicken, no, unwrap it first‚Ä¶</p>
<p>The work goes on. The great work goes on.</p>
