<p>‚ÄìSomething‚Äôs wrong with the math chip. Every one of them gives the exact same error, for just one pair of operands. Weird huh?</p>
<p>‚ÄìWell tell them we want a fix.</p>
<p>‚ÄìThey won‚Äôt talk to me, they want you. We put out an advisory on the Internet. About a million users want that fix now.</p>
<p>‚ÄìI don‚Äôt have time to handle every little thing like this, this should be a, a warranty repair.</p>
<p>‚ÄìBelieve me, I tried.</p>
<p>‚ÄìAll right, I‚Äôll call. Now I really have to‚Ä¶ but as soon as Conor was out the door he paused at Lab Hiring Criticized, frowning as if it were some vermin that unchecked would spread.</p>
<p>‚ÄìJ Frank Greer, please. Philip Quine, tell him it‚Äôs urgent‚Ä¶ Waiting with the phone to his ear he tapped a computer key.</p>
