<p>‚ÄìAre you coming to bed?</p>
<p>‚ÄìWhat? Oh, oh yes, in, in just a minute, I was just‚Ä¶ looking back in surprise at the papers in his lap, ‚ÄìI just‚Ä¶ [pg301]</p>
<p>‚ÄìPhilip, I‚Äôm crying.</p>
<p>‚ÄìWhat‚Ä¶? The hall light behind her slim figure, slouched there in white briefs and chemise, rushing him with regret, for Nan, for Kate, for Sorokin, for everything in his life that was or would become irretrievable.</p>
