<p>‚ÄìThey‚Äôre lo fat. She laid down Nanopreneuring and held out a thinwalled box, where a stressed tab and slot threatened to give way until Quine grabbed the sagging edge. ‚ÄìBernd Dietz wants to see you.</p>
<p>‚ÄìTell him I‚Äôm busy. Tell him Monday. [pg306]</p>
<p>The box pushed papers across the desk, exposing, like a thorn he couldn‚Äôt pluck out, <em>Nancy Julia Adams</em> and <em>Benjamin Daniel Stern</em> still awaiting the pleasure of is company, or at least the earnest of it, on <em>16 July 1994 RSVP</em>. He hid them under System Requirements, but they emerged unabashed minutes later from Laser Compression of Matter, as he held aloft the doughnut to lose them again beneath Steganography: A Novel Method of Data Hiding. On the computer screen was another thorn still awaiting a response he was as unready to give as to forego.</p>
