<p>‚ÄìBut that‚Äôs just it, I‚Äôm surrounded by all these bad choices, bad ideas, relics of some past, there are whole groups, departments, sections devoted to them, we have contracts and deliverables, it‚Äôs like a maze you have to run, there‚Äôs no time to, to reflect on what direction you should take just get to the next corner and go on from there.</p>
<p>‚ÄìYes, I know. Sometimes I think it‚Äôs impossible. That you can‚Äôt convert these entrenched ideas. That nothing good can ever come of them. That we‚Äôd have to close down all the weapons labs. And even then it wouldn‚Äôt end. It does seem impossible sometimes. But</p>
<p>‚ÄìBut I mean, how do you keep on with it when you see how impossible it is?</p>
