<p>‚ÄìTo halt‚Ä¶? Oh but‚Ä¶ something like alarm rose in him. ‚ÄìBut you know it already went in. The Conceptual Design Report. The secretary okayed it. The baseline budget was accepted, I mean it won‚Äôt be formally approved for a few months, but, but even Chase signed off. It [pg332] looks like a sure thing, even the x-ray laser, we‚Ä¶ Lynn? She was on her feet, standing against that flawless sky, fighting it seemed for breath.</p>
<p>‚ÄìWhat? When did this. Did you.</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn</p>
<p>‚ÄìHow long have you known?</p>
<p>‚ÄìIt just I just</p>
<p>‚ÄìEven, going into that meeting last night, you knew? And all my. You. You‚Äôd think. By now you‚Äôd think that I.</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn‚Ä¶ he scrambled up to follow her pacing.</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou mean that everything we‚Äôve talked about, Chase, Turner, Sorokin, the public hearing, you‚Äôre saying it‚Äôs all wasted because this decision was, was made. Like Tony said, it was a done deal. And I believed that you really wanted to to to</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn, I did want, I do‚Ä¶</p>
<p>‚ÄìAll my experience with politicians and I wasn‚Äôt ready for this. Damn!</p>
<p>‚ÄìBut‚Ä¶ he reached for her.</p>
<p>‚ÄìDon‚Äôt! Don‚Äôt you understand, my own foolishness that‚Äôs bad enough but how I‚Äôve behaved, used up favors, credibility, thrown CANT‚Äôs resources into this, because damn it I trusted you, thought you were being honest that there was a, a chance to turn it around‚Ä¶ and now this, this makes me feel so stupid!</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn, please, isn‚Äôt there more between us than‚Ä¶ stepping up to where she whirled in dappled sun to push him away, ‚ÄìDon‚Äôt! as his heel turned on a loose stone, gave under him, and toppled him into the brush. Under his hand and against his face were the waxy green leaves and white berries of Rhus or Toxicodendron.</p>
<p>‚ÄìOh God. Wait, let me, she bent to unscrew the cap from a water bottle as he thrashed upward. ‚ÄìDon‚Äôt touch me! I mean, wait, just lie there while I‚Ä¶ as she wet a kerchief he gazed at the burning sky. She dabbed at his face.</p>
<p>‚ÄìShut your eyes. This is to get the plant oil off, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/urushiol" title="Wikipedia: urushiol">urushiol</a>. Your skin oil will protect you for an hour or two. When you get home, take a cool shower. Don‚Äôt use soap or hot water, they‚Äôll break down your skin oil before the urushiol. [pg333]</p>
<p>‚ÄìAren‚Äôt you coming home with me?</p>
<p>She dabbed in silence at his hands and forearms. She folded the kerchief and poured water from the bottle over her hands one at a time, then threw kerchief and bottle into her pack.</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn‚Ä¶</p>
<p>‚ÄìI‚Äôll see you at the car.</p>
<p>She turned from him and went steadily into the sun, where, ruffled by a wind, her hair spread out in fiery points. The sunlight was so bright now it was hollow, the reality leached from everything. It was a few minutes before he followed. She was waiting near the gate, across the circle from the car, and came toward it only when he unlocked the doors.</p>
<p>They drove in silence down the winding white road to the freeway.</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou weren‚Äôt such a bad choice. The x-ray laser, that‚Äôs the real kicker, that you hated so much, now you‚Äôre protecting it.</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn it‚Äôs not the, the Superbright it‚Äôs</p>
<p>‚ÄìMaybe if you solve your Quine scattering problem all those undead Reagan assholes can bring their missile defense back to life.</p>
<p>‚ÄìThat‚Äôs not what</p>
<p>‚ÄìGod I‚Äôm so mad at you! We‚Äôre keeping our bombs no matter what so fuck you.</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn, I said, you know, if you wanted to have an impact you should, you could have come on board with us, you say you‚Äôre trying to go to law school but</p>
<p>‚ÄìPhilip, don‚Äôt say anything more.</p>
<p>At a red light he looked away from the barrel of the traffic camera to FAST DIVORCE BANKRUPTCY on a bus stop bench.</p>
<p>‚ÄìLynn please, I didn‚Äôt mean‚Ä¶ will you let me‚Ä¶</p>
<p>‚ÄìCANT‚Äôs sending me back to Geneva. For the second CTBT session. It starts May sixteenth. I‚Äôll be gone six weeks.</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou didn‚Äôt tell me.</p>
<p>‚ÄìI was waiting for you to ask.</p>
<p>‚ÄìBut I didn‚Äôt know, how could I‚Ä¶</p>
<p>‚ÄìTo ask about, I don‚Äôt know, about anything that‚Äôs important to me.</p>
<p>He reached for her and she backed away. ‚ÄìI really don‚Äôt want poison [pg334] oak.</p>
<p>After she‚Äôd gone inside he watched a cloud of insects move in and out of sun. At home in the shower he turned the water as hot as possible. He stood laving and scrubbing until his skin was red.</p>
</section>
<section id="six-1" class="level3">
<h3>Six</h3>
<p>[pg335] ‚Äìten minutes we‚Äôll bring you the world, which suddenly loomed closer in the form of HOW AM I DRIVING? CALL 1-800-328-7448 as he braked and ‚ÄìNorth Korea said it‚Äôs started withdrawing spent fuel from a nucular reactor without international inspectors present, an action that senior US officials warned, pressing ^ for the blue blink of JAM where a red Miata SFORZA was parked between a Mercedes and a dumpster CREDNE Waste Management. As he released the seat belt he caught a glimpse of himself in the rearview mirror, the left half of a face distended in forsakenness and misery, and swollen with welts now crusting and beginning to weep clear fluid. He dabbed with a handkerchief already stiff and yellowed, holding it there through Soon Yet OPEN Visa Mastercard PUSH, from blinding heat into bone chill, a crowded foyer, and up to an impassive Chinese, ‚ÄìExcuse me, is Leo Highet, who pointed to a table behind a potted ficus.</p>
