<p>‚ÄìHyundai, that‚Äôs cute. Suppose it‚Äôs true. How will Pyongyang react when they hear that their neighbor to the south is checking out a missile defense component? Look, this data is the camel‚Äôs nose. If Gate‚Äôs CRADA goes through, the whole package is out there, thrusters, sensors, everything. The North Koreans are very resourceful. Our intel keeps saying they‚Äôre on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North%20Korean%20famine" title="Wikipedia: North Korean famine">the verge of economic collapse</a>, yet somehow they hang on. Somehow they‚Äôve built nuclear reactors, missiles, sure they had Russian and Chinese help but not lately, and they were always smart enough to play the two off against each other. You‚Äôve got to admire the feisty little fucks.</p>
