<p>‚ÄìWell, Philip, truth is a story. Or do you know better than that? Help me out here. What‚Äôs the truth of your situation?</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou‚Äôve got some some some‚Ä¶ after you‚Ä¶</p>
<p>‚ÄìAfter I what? Tried to keep my Lab going in the face of impossible demands, incoherent policy, and ignorant policy makers? You getting a taste of that now? Ever had to explain anything to a congressman?</p>
<p>‚ÄìChase‚Ä¶</p>
<p>‚ÄìThink Chase is your friend, the very first time you forget to say mother may I he‚Äôll be on you like a wolverine. No, believe it or not I‚Äôm here to help you Philip. So don‚Äôt insult me. Don‚Äôt make yourself out to [pg339] be the victim, sitting in that chair you pulled out from under me. Pissing me off will only make me irrational and vindictive. Didn‚Äôt you have something to ask me?</p>
<p>‚ÄìWho‚Äôs Devon Null?</p>
<p>‚ÄìTalented physicist. I think he‚Äôs on Wall Street now. Using chaos theory to model financial trends.</p>
<p>‚ÄìRecords show he was never an employee.</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou don‚Äôt say.</p>
