<p>‚ÄìIt was my office. He was never there. Nullpoint, what is that?</p>
<p>‚ÄìI have no idea.</p>
<p>‚ÄìConor recovered the deleted partition on your computer.</p>
<p>Highet set down his chopsticks and touched a napkin to his mouth. He chewed in silence for a moment, then looked around the room, as if someone out there might be easier to talk to. ‚ÄìWhat a great kid. Isn‚Äôt he a great kid? Okay, about Nullpoint. You‚Äôve probably never read your contract, but ass an employee of the University of California, you agreed to certain things. ‚ÄúIn the even that any such invention shall be deemed by University to be patentable, I shall do all things necessary to assign to University all rights, title and interest therein.‚Äù See, people at the Lab commit to an unusual scientific career. They do classified research that can‚Äôt be published. They invent things they can‚Äôt patent or sell. Occasionally the Lab waives commercial rights, but it‚Äôs always a pain in the ass, especially now that the university‚Äôs gotten so <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayh-Dole%20Act" title="Wikipedia: Bayh-Dole Act">greedy about patents</a>. So we set up a shell company. To shelter intellectual property.</p>
<p>‚ÄìIt‚Äôs, it‚Äôs all about the money for you, isn‚Äôt it?</p>
<p>‚ÄìWhat‚Äôs it all about for you, Philip? Being right? I could care less about the money. I did this for my people. If they feel they‚Äôre getting ripped off they‚Äôll rip you off.</p>
<p>‚ÄìThat would explain the forty million in missing inventory. How many people have profited from this setup?</p>
<p>‚ÄìProfited. Maybe once in a great while somebody got enough to pay off a loan. Profit? That‚Äôs change that fell out on the car seat. Christ Philip you bought a house with the rise in your salary, you know [pg340] what‚Äôs being tossed around. You want to talk real money, ask Dan Root. He‚Äôs the one with irons in the fire. I‚Äôm just a semi-retired consultant with condo payments to make and white papers to write. Or ask Rector, he‚Äôs already looked into this.</p>
<p>‚ÄìSo everybody thinks they‚Äôre entitled, is that right? Employees running insider land deals, walking out the door with equipment, taking kickbacks from patent agreements, you think that‚Äôs, that‚Äôs, there‚Äôs a GAO report on my desk about twelve thousand missing documents, nuclear weapons designs, x-ray laser plans, photos of tests, did any of those documents pass through Nullpoint?</p>
<p>Highet shook his head again and lowered it, as if tired of contending with missed points, to push the remains of a dumpling through a dark sauce on his plate. Quine put the coyote fetish on the table.</p>
<p>‚ÄìThe thing about passwords, you should use a random string, never a real word. Seven characters minimum. Put some numbers and punctuation marks in it. And never write it down. But does anyone follow these simple rules? Highet put aside his chopsticks, then picked up the fetish and put it in his jacket pocket, ‚ÄìYou have any other questions for me?</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou worked on fusion for quite a while.</p>
<p>‚ÄìAnd many before me. Szabo‚Ä¶ R√©ti‚Ä¶</p>
