<p>‚ÄìYou really despise me, don‚Äôt you, Philip. You think I stole secrets, you think I faked data, why don‚Äôt you call the fucking FBI if you‚Äôre so sure. If you‚Äôve read my laser fusion papers you know the science is good. Despite how you feel about me.</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou were always after the money.</p>
<p>‚ÄìYou amaze me. Only someone who doesn‚Äôt know what the fuck he‚Äôs talking about could be so sure. You know Bill Venham? No? Close friend of Dan Root. Ran direct mail for Goldwater. Claims he got Reagan elected governor in sixty six<a href="#fn157" class="footnoteRef" id="fnref157"><sup>157</sup></a>. Now he runs the Arete Foundation, heard of them? No? They own NOUS. They own broadcasters. They fund right wing causes. That loudmouth Eubanks on the radio? Venham [pg341] started him out eight years ago on a Sacramento station. They want to shut down DOE, give all the nuclear weapons work to the Pentagon, you think DOE‚Äôs fucked up talk to some ambitious Air Force colonel‚Äôs read too much <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom%20Clancy" title="Wikipedia: Tom Clancy">Tom Clancy</a>. Bill wants creationism taught in the schools, he‚Äôs got Senator Bangerter on board for that one. Oh, and Bill sponsors the Hertz fellowships. You‚Äôve heard of those. At least I know where my money comes from.</p>
<p>Highet pushed back his chair. ‚ÄìIf you‚Äôve had the time to crack my PGP, you must have found those GIF files on my disk. Not my thing, but I wondered why the hell they were on an open server, so I saved copies. Ask Conor about steganography. You‚Äôre so clever, you‚Äôll work it out.</p>
