<p>‚ÄìYeah, I think so. Tell me Philip, you ever get any joy out of life?</p>
<p>‚ÄìJoy‚Ä¶?</p>
<p>Highet regarded him with the dour look of a man who‚Äôs missed a long-awaited chance. He dropped a few bills on the table. ‚ÄìThis is my treat.</p>
<p>The red Miata was gone when Quine emerged under a sky full of Mie scattering, a haze that magnified the sunlight by diffusing it into almost an opacity settled over the bridge as an unyielding glare while the battering of crosswinds tore free the fluttering Profit From Your Knowledge from under his wiper blade, and an orotund voice proposed that someone or something ‚Äìwouldn‚Äôt stand a prayer, before being silenced by a quick thumb jabbing 5 for the temporary solitude of brushed steel doors and ‚ÄìThe hell‚Ä¶? a breastwork of boxes stacked in the front office.</p>
<p>‚ÄìThe Conceptual Design Report is back from the printers. They sent ten copies.</p>
<p>‚ÄìGood God I can‚Äôt get by them, how did</p>
<p>‚ÄìIt‚Äôs twenty seven volumes.</p>
<p>‚ÄìWell can‚Äôt we‚Ä¶ ow! What‚Äôs</p>
