<p>‚ÄìHumanitas, yes, that‚Äôs what we need, isn‚Äôt it, Highet with his Renaissance, and Aldus Manutius there, need a few more particle men who‚Äôve read the Tao Te Ching, couple more managers who‚Äôve studied Sun Tzu, lend these binary views a little tone, dress up the winners and losers, the Elect and the Preterite, the screwers and the screwed, each man in his station. Keep your distance from the Preterite, can‚Äôt have just anyone winning, because if you let the rabble win, if they can rise, you can surely fall.</p>
<p>Nolan folded back pages, ‚ÄìListen to this lovely bit, ‚Äúthe support of this tight-knit community‚Äù, support is it now? I‚Äôd have said the goading, the ambition, the <em>Schadenfreude</em>, that‚Äôs what gets the work done. Look around you, these are people without lives, the wife walked out six months ago with the kid, they‚Äôre eating Campbell‚Äôs soup cold out of the can, they haven‚Äôt got a clean shirt, but after a few months of eighteen-hour days they‚Äôve got <em>data</em> that everyone wants to see. They <em>win big</em>.</p>
<p>‚ÄìBran, you keep working here.</p>
